{
  "title": "About Htv Plugin",
  "story": [
    {
      "type": "markdown",
      "id": "a5b9ab1e17aae0d0",
      "text": "The **Htv Plugin** renders Hitchhiker.tv live media surfaces directly inside a wiki item. It is the first plugin form of the live camera, VDO.Ninja, and Three.js surface experiments."
    },
    {
      "type": "htv",
      "id": "a417bde970f7f4db",
      "text": "TITLE Hitchhiker.tv Plugin Surface\nMODE SHATTER\nHEIGHT 620\nVDO https://vdo.ninja/?view=hitchhiker-tv-test&cleanoutput"
    },
    {
      "type": "markdown",
      "id": "163563e5996781b4",
      "text": "## Item Text\n\nCommands follow the Federated Wiki DSL convention: uppercase first word for commands, optional colon accepted.\n\n- `TITLE` sets the panel title.\n- `MODE` chooses `SWARM`, `SHATTER`, `PORTAL`, or `NOVA`.\n- `HEIGHT` sets the item height in pixels.\n- `VDO` provides an optional VDO.Ninja view URL.\n- `ROOM` names a VDO.Ninja room for the Join Room and Watch Room buttons. Without it, a room name is derived from the item id, so forks of the page share the same room.\n\n`NOVA` blasts the tiles apart in periodic explosions. Clicking any surface spins it through the depth plane, with a ripple spreading from the click point, before it eases back into place."
    },
    {
      "type": "markdown",
      "id": "0c0dd9c01c1d8a68",
      "text": "## Repositories\n\n- [https://github.com/Hitchhikers-Guide-to-the-Galaxy/wiki-plugin-htv github]\n- [https://www.npmjs.com/package/wiki-plugin-htv npm]"
    }
  ],
